Atlantic Schooners.label: Atlantic Schooners
Atlantic Schooners.description: The Atlantic Schooners were a conditional Canadian Football League expansion team that was to begin play in 1984 out of Dartmouth, Nova Scotia. Wikipedia

Baltimore Stallions.label: Baltimore Stallions
Baltimore Stallions.description: The Baltimore Stallions were a Canadian Football League team based in Baltimore, Maryland, United States, which played the 1994 and 1995 seasons. Wikipedia

Birmingham Barracudas.label: Birmingham Barracudas
Birmingham Barracudas.description: The Birmingham Barracudas were a Canadian football team that played the 1995 season in the Canadian Football League. The Barracudas were part of a failed attempt to expand the CFL into the United States. Wikipedia

Shreveport Pirates.label: Shreveport Pirates
Shreveport Pirates.description: The Shreveport Pirates were a Canadian Football League team, playing at Independence Stadium in Shreveport, Louisiana, USA, in 1994 and 1995. They were known to be one of the least successful of the CFL's American franchises on and off the field. Wikipedia

Sacramento Gold Miners.label: Sacramento Gold Miners
Sacramento Gold Miners.description: The Sacramento Gold Miners were a Canadian football team based in Sacramento, California. The franchise was the first American team in the Canadian Football League. Wikipedia

San Antonio Texans.label: San Antonio Texans
San Antonio Texans.description: The San Antonio Texans were a Canadian Football League team that played in the Alamodome in San Antonio, Texas, in the 1995 CFL season. They had relocated from Sacramento, California, where the team had been called the Sacramento Gold Miners. Wikipedia

Toronto Argonauts.label: Toronto Argonauts
Toronto Argonauts.description: The Toronto Argonauts are a professional Canadian football team competing in the East Division of the Canadian Football League. Wikipedia

BC Lions.label: BC Lions
BC Lions.description: The BC Lions are a professional Canadian football team competing in the West Division of the Canadian Football League. Based in Vancouver, British Columbia, the Lions play their home games at BC Place in Downtown Vancouver. Wikipedia

Hamilton Tiger-Cats.label: Hamilton Tiger-Cats
Hamilton Tiger-Cats.description: The Hamilton Tiger-Cats are a professional Canadian football team based in Hamilton, Ontario, founded in 1950 with the merger of the Hamilton Tigers and the Hamilton Wildcats. Wikipedia

Edmonton Eskimos.label: Edmonton Eskimos
Edmonton Eskimos.description: The Edmonton Eskimos are a professional Canadian football team based in Edmonton, Alberta, competing in the West Division of the Canadian Football League. Wikipedia

Montreal Alouettes.label: Montreal Alouettes
Montreal Alouettes.description: The Montreal Alouettes are a Canadian Football League team based in Montreal, Quebec. Founded in 1946, the team has folded and been revived twice. The Alouettes compete in the CFL Eastern Division and last won the Grey Cup championship in 2010. Wikipedia

Saskatchewan Roughriders.label: Saskatchewan Roughriders
Saskatchewan Roughriders.description: The Saskatchewan Roughriders are a professional football team based in Regina, Saskatchewan who play in the West Division of the Canadian Football League. Founded in 1910, they have played their games at Mosaic Stadium at Taylor Field since 1936. Wikipedia

Winnipeg Blue Bombers.label: Winnipeg Blue Bombers
Winnipeg Blue Bombers.description: The Winnipeg Blue Bombers are a Canadian football team based in Winnipeg, Manitoba. They are currently members of the West Division of the Canadian Football League. Wikipedia

Las Vegas Posse.label: Las Vegas Posse
Las Vegas Posse.description: The Las Vegas Posse was a Canadian Football League team that played the 1994 season as part of the CFL's short-lived American expansion. The Posse was one of the least successful CFL teams, both on the field and off. Wikipedia

Memphis Mad Dogs.label: Memphis Mad Dogs
Memphis Mad Dogs.description: The Memphis Mad Dogs were a Canadian football team that played the 1995 season in the Canadian Football League. The Mad Dogs were part of a failed attempt to expand the CFL into the United States. Wikipedia

Ottawa Renegades.label: Ottawa Renegades
Ottawa Renegades.description: Ottawa Renegades was the most recent name of a Canadian Football League team based in Ottawa, Ontario founded in 2002, seven years after the storied Ottawa Rough Riders folded. Wikipedia

Ottawa Canadian Football League team.label: Ottawa Redblacks
Ottawa Canadian Football League team.description: The Ottawa RedBlacks are a Canadian Football League franchise that has been awarded to the city of Ottawa, Ontario. Wikipedia

Ottawa Rough Riders.label: Ottawa Rough Riders
Ottawa Rough Riders.description: The Ottawa Rough Riders were a Canadian Football League team based in Ottawa, Ontario, founded in 1876. Wikipedia
